<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910819-0027</DOCNO><DOCID>910819-0027.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- McDonnell Douglas Corp.:   Firm Gets Radar Contract   For Estimated $257 Million</HL><DATE>08/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8</SO><CO>   GM GMH MD</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)AUTOMOBILES (AUT)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)MICHIGAN (MI)MISSOURI (MO)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   McDonnell Douglas Corp. said it and Hughes Aircraft Co., aunit of General Motors Corp., signed a production contractestimated at $257 million for an improved radar for the U.S.Navy's F/A-18 Hornet strike fighter.   The agreement covers the production of 12 radars. Deliveryof the Hornet fighters with the new radar is expected tobegin in June 1994.</LP><TEXT>   Separately, McDonnell Douglas, based in St. Louis, saidits McDonnell Space Systems Co. was selected by the StrategicDefense Initiative Organization to design a prototypesingle-stage-to-orbit vehicle for $58.9 million. The reusablelaunch vehicle is to be capable of boosting 20,000 pounds ofcargo to a low Earth orbit, the aerospace company said.</TEXT></DOC>